    <section name="Modules of Eoulsan">

      <p>Eoulsan contains many modules to perform analysis. As Eoulsan can work in two (local an distributed) modes, some modules are available for the two and some for only one.</p>  

	<table>
		<tr><th>Phase/Module</th><th>Local Mode</th><th>Distributed mode</th></tr>
		<tr><td>Create design</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Upload design data</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Create SOAP index</td><td>Yes</td><td>No (available in upload design data)</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Filter reads</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Map reads</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Filter and map reads</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Filter samples</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Expression</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
		<tr><td>Differential analysis</td><td>Yes</td><td>No</td></tr>
	</table>

	<p>You can get the list of available modules with: </p>
<source>
$ eoulsan.sh help
</source>

	<p>Help for each module can be shown with:</p>
<source>
$ eoulsan.sh module -h
</source>
      
    </section>


